    "Note that the prefactor of e ± 1 2 (iq 1 +iq 2) in V w m 1,m 2 for even w has a trivial OPE with e -Σ so plays JHEP04(2024)048no role.",
    "This OPE is not specific to any choice of m 1 or m 2, meaning it works equally well whether we impose (3.4) or (3.6).Hence, if we insert e -Σ(z) inside a correlator and take the limit z → z k,e -Σ(z) n-2+2g α=1 W (u α) n i=1 V w i m i 1,m i 2 (x i; z i) n-2+2g α=1 W (u α) n i=1 V w i m i 1,m i 2 (x i; z i) = x k + a k (z -z k) w k + O((z -z k) w k +1),wherea k = n-2+2g α=1 W (u α) i̸ =k V w i m i 1,m i 2 (x i; z i) V w k m k 1 -1/2,m k 2 -1/2 (x k; z k) n-2+2g α=1 W (u α) n i=1 V w i m i 1,m i 2 (x i; z i).",
    "(4.5)The shift in the values of m k 1 and m k 2 is such that the constraint (3.15) is preserved, meaning that the numerator is generically non-zero.",
